All Classes

  • Class Description
    AICompiler
    Compiles external AI code.
    Car
    Represents a car in the game.
    Car.Color
    Used to describe the color of the car.
    CarPanel
    JPanel extension which contains all settings for a car and GUI to change them.
    Checkpoint
    Represents a checkpoint in the game.
    CrosshairTile
    Represents one tile of the crosshair used by human players to control their cars.
    DataReader
    Reads the map files, the tile-set file and the file lists.
    DriverAI
    Interface for writing your own AI for this game.
    Game
    Manages the game.
    Main
    Initializes the application, switches between menu and game.
    Map
    Represents the tiled map in the game.
    MapFormatException
    Exception which is thrown if there is no start on the map or there is more than one start or if there is no finish.
    Menu
    Manages the menu, all its components and all its functions.
    Resources
    Loads all image resources for the game and saves them as BufferedImage instances.
    ScorePanel
    Contains post-game info about one car and how has it placed in the race.
    Tile
    Represents all possible tile types.
